<TEXT>
mexico has recorded its lowest inflation rate 
in a decade and junes 12 percent increase in consumer prices put 
the 12month inflation rate at 176 percent the bank of mexico 
reports 
inflation hit an alltime high of 1592 percent in 1987 then 
dropped to 517 percent in 1988 
junes was the lowest increase in the consumer price index since 
july 1979 and brought inflation for the six months ending june 30 to 
93 percent 
it was also the lowest for a first semester since 1978 when 
prices rose by an average of 84 percent the bank said sunday in 
its monthly report 
economists tie the sharp drop in inflation to a government 
agreement with labor and management instituted in late 1987 that 
freezes wages and prices for an average of six months at a time and 
keeps increases at a minimum 
during the last round of talks all three sides agreed july 1 to 
raise the minimum wage by an average of 65 percent nationwide and 
continue the program until next march with another round of 
negotiations in december 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

