us district judge robert aguilar pleaded 
innocent today to charges of using his office to do favors for 
convicted felons crimes punishable by up to 55 years in prison 
aguilar the fourth federal judge in the nation to be indicted in 
the last decade and the first ever for racketeering was arraigned 
before a visiting federal judge howard bratton of new mexico and 
released without bail his trial has also been assigned to an 
outside judge louis bechtle of philadelphia 
the 58yearold judge stood with his lawyers for less than three 
minutes before the bench and spoke only a few words identifying 
himself giving his age and saying the plea is not guilty 
before bratton said further reading of the charges was not necessary 
bratton denied a request by justice department prosecutor ralph 
martin to prohibit aguilar from contacting potential witnesses 
defense lawyer patrick hallinan told reporters the request would 
have barred aguilar from speaking to half of his family and 
described it as part of the governments campaign to portray aguilar 
as a corrupt judge 
aguilar left through a rear exit and did not speak with 
reporters before the hearing he sat talking and laughing with 
defense lawyers and did not look at codefendants rudy tham an 
imprisoned former labor leader and abe chapman a selfstyled 
former mobster related to aguilar by marriage 
aguilar a 1980 appointee of president jimmy carter was indicted 
by a federal grand jury last month on eight felony charges he has 
relinquished most of his duties while the case is pending 
