companies by printing money or borrowing abroad 
neither avenue is open to menem who was elected may 14 the 
nation is 45 billion in arrears in interest payments on the 60 
billion foreign debt the austral valued at 18 per 1 in february 
has lost 97 percent of its value in five months 
inflation and devaluations touched off a recession in which real 
wages have fallen by at least 35 percent this year and unemployment 
has climbed to 10 percent 
