walesa is proud of the house he purchased and renovated last year 
with earnings from his autobiography a way of hope 
a stuccoed brick singlefamily house that would raise no eyebrows 
in the united states or western europe it is a dwelling that many 
poles would regard as a palace compared to their typically cramped 
apartments 
it has a garden and small orchard where walesa will take bush for 
a stroll and space enough for a home office filled with mementoes 
walesa also has a satellite dish to pull in foreign television 
broadcasts on his color television 
the dining room is decorated with paintings of nature scenes and 
religious themes in the living room hangs a portrait of polishborn 
pope john paul ii my highest authority walesa calls him 
when walesa was traveling the country last fall meeting workers 
in the aftermath of a wave of strikes he sometimes had to explain 
the house to followers who feared he was putting on airs 
look i wrote a book he would answer i have eight kids 
the explanation usually sufficed 
after lunch bush will visit the workers monument outside the 
lenin shipyard where solidarity was born in august 1980 
danuta walesa 39 has put her friend grazyna pusz in charge of 
cooking for the bushes mrs puszs husband krzysztof is walesas 
longtime assistant 
the menu includes simple and wholesome polish dishes in an array 
that should make the walesas table groan 
appetizers will include smoked salmon and smoked eel the latter 
a gdansk specialty and a tray of polish cold cuts 
chlodnik a cold summertime soup made from beets and sour 
cream and mushroom soup will be next with the main course to 
include turkey veal pork with mushrooms beef and new potatoes 
dessert will be a jelly made from wild strawberries chocolate 
cake and a strawberry pie 
mrs walesa said she planned to just be sitting doing nothing 
and enjoying being the guest i trust my friend 
</TEXT>
