peck was able to respond with a back copy of a us geology 
magazine that had been hastily gathered up by an aide 
obviously embarassed by the fact that the americans had not 
prepared for an exchange of gifts peck told the soviets we start 
this off by our owing you one 
the agreement calls for american and soviet geologists to 
exchange the results of research conducted in their respective 
countries it eventually will lead to an exchange of field trips 
that will involve the study of various geological formations in the 
two countries the two countries reached the agreement after two 
years of negotiation and the ceremony monday marked the formal 
exchange of copies of the signed agreement 
