provided by the canadian firm nordion is used to sterilize the 
equipment 
lemus said the accident resulted purely from human error and 
that the salvadoran ministry of labor had determined there was no 
negligence on the part of the plant 
but one of those injured said the accident was caused by 
mechanical failure 
the source of radiation got stuck im the mechanic on duty i 
had to work on it francisco roque tobar said 
he spoke from a mexico city hospital where he and jose luis 
martinez were being treated the hospital would not disclose their 
conditions but tobar said one of his legs was amputated last week 
lemus said tobar 26 and two other employees entered a chamber 
in which a rod of cobalt 60 had failed to return to a safe position 
in a protective pool of water 
tobar failed to use a portable radiation monitor and he and the 
other two men apparently ignored an alarm system warning them that 
something was wrong lemus said 
tobar said he wasnt wearing a monitor but that the alarm system 
goes off so frequently that he ignored it 
you have to go in to repair the equipment tobar said 
canadian press quoted nordion spokeswoman donna coates as saying 
two company engineers arrived in el salvador on feb 12 to help with 
the malfunctioning equipment but were not told there had been a 
serious accident 
they got the rod to return to the protective pool and rendered 
the equipment inoperable the canadian news agency said 
