maintained a paneuropean manufacturing approach 
it made business sense to treat europe as an entity said ibm 
spokesman john wells in paris 
ibm has a dozen manufacturing plants in the eec countries more 
than 90 percent of the products it sells in europe are made in 
europe 
other companies are strengthening their positions 
