acquisitions worth 14 billion in the trading bloc according to 
martin sikora editor of the philadelphiabased magazine mergers amp 
acquisitions 
the number of deals rose to 107 valued at 24 billion in 1987 
and amounted to 82 worth 21 billion last year most were in 
food pharmaceuticals industrial equipment and electronics and 
computers 
it allows larger stronger more aggressive companies to play 
in this vast market sikora said 
