it is a miners term for a thin seam of coal maybe 40 inches 
thick where it takes unusual stooping and bending and crawling to 
dig it out low coal chapman stands about 55 
he was referring to an episode at nearby blair mountain in 1921 
when company detectives sheriffs deputies and federal troops 
