the idea but told them the work couldnt be categorized so they 
couldnt put it out 
curley admits the book is difficult to describe 
its not really parody and its not really satire she said 
i can tell you everything its not i really have trouble defining 
what it is its more imagination 
in mid1987 ten speed gave curley and blumenthal one year to 
write the complete time traveler during a brainstorming 
session the authors came up with their own version of time travel 
a belt that enables people to slip inside wormholes by raising the 
bodys vibration level to that of a wormhole 
while there is no proof wormholes exist some physicists believe 
the supposed holes in space and time possibly could be used as a 
tunnel to return to another era or to travel to distant parts of the 
universe that notion has its roots in albert einsteins special 
relativity theory which deals with the relationships among space 
time matter and energy and includes his formula energy equals 
mass times the speed of light squared the theory says the speed of 
light is constant regardless of whether the source of light is 
moving curley spent weeks acquainting herself with the latest 
scientific thought on time travel she also frequented the local 
library to gather historical trivia for her chapter on time travel 
destinations 
she learned for example that julius caesar banned delivery 
carts in the daytime because of traffic jams forcing carts to be 
unloaded at night time travelers therefore are advised to nap 
during the day when visiting rome in the first century bc 
she also learned that during the indianapolis speedways opening 
on aug 21 1909 charles merzs car blew a tire on the south turn 
of the last race killing two spectators and a mechanic time 
travelers consequently are urged to avoid the south turn area 
the authors found the no 1 attraction in earths history to be 
jesus sermon on the mount 
what we decided curley explained smiling is that of 
these many many many thousands of people who were there there 
were really only about 22 natives the rest were all tourists 
because how did all those people know when to show up 
</TEXT>
