<TEXT>
here are some things to know about reverse mortgages and some 
sources of further information 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
tenure or lifetime mortgages guarantee homeowners monthly 
checks for as long as they live or occupy the house as a principal 
residence 
term loans offer monthly checks for a specific number of 
years 
lineofcredit loans let borrowers draw payments of any size 
or frequency up to some maximum amount 
shared appreciation mortgages share property value increases 
with the lender and are offered in combination with term and 
lifetime mortgages generally resulting in a lower interest rate 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
tests can include application fees closing costs interest 
sales commissions and future appreciation 
eligibility generally begins at age 62 and homeowners must be 
free from mortgage debt or have only a small balance 
interest generally ranging from 8 percent to 121 percent and 
mortgages can be fixedrate or adjustable 
</TEXT>
