<TEXT>
when nike inc went public in 1980 business week 
magazine wondered whether the athletic shoe makers move to the 
stock market meant that the jogging craze had run its course 
now at the other end of the decade the company named for the 
greek goddess of victory is planning for future success around 
peoples continuing fascination with fitness 
people said nike has helped but also has taken a ride on the 
running boom said nike cofounder philip h knight what we 
used to call the running boom was really just the first shot of the 
fitness revolution 
knight nikes chairman and chief executive officer said in an 
interview that he believes this revolution has led to lifestyle 
changes that will keep the momentum rolling for sales of athletic 
shoes 
working out has become a habit for more people whether they 
like it or not because they know its good for them said knight 
you might get bored with sleeping but youve still got to do it 
knight was in new york on monday to for a news conference the 
first in the beaverton orebased companys history to release 
nikes latest financial results 
